1Ô∏è‚É£ Vehicle Popup Height + Width

Right now, the Vehicle popup size is hardcoded in your Index.cshtml inside the kendoWindow initialization:

$("#estimatePopup").kendoWindow({
    modal: true,
    width: 1200,   // üëà width hardcoded here
    height: "auto", // üëà currently auto
    resizable: false,
    scrollable: false,
    title: "Estimate",
    visible: false,
    actions: ["Close"]
});


üëâ If you want to increase height by ~10%:

Replace height: "auto" with a fixed percentage of viewport. Example:

height: "88vh", // ~10% taller than default 80vh


Width you can keep the same (1200px) or make it relative (80vw).

So your Vehicle popup config should look like this:

$("#estimatePopup").kendoWindow({
    modal: true,
    width: "80vw",   // responsive width
    height: "88vh",  // ~10% taller than before
    resizable: false,
    scrollable: false,
    title: "Estimate",
    visible: false,
    actions: ["Close"]
});


That way, all popups (Vehicle & Stock Coded) are consistent in size and scale with screen resolution.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Tabs ‚Üí Ribbon Style (sleek, less space)

By default, Kendo tabs eat up vertical space. You want something more like a ribbon strip at the top.

Here‚Äôs CSS to make them slim & modern:

/* ==========================================
   TABS ‚Üí Sleek Ribbon Style
========================================== */
#estimateTabs .k-tabstrip-items {
    display: flex;
    background: #f5faff; /* very light blue ribbon */
    border-bottom: 1px solid #b3d1ff;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
}

#estimateTabs .k-tabstrip-items .k-item {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
}

#estimateTabs .k-tabstrip-items .k-link {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #000;
    padding: 4px 12px !important;  /* sleek padding */
    min-height: 22px !important;   /* slim height */
    line-height: 20px !important;
    border-radius: 0;
    transition: background 0.2s ease-in-out;
}

/* Hover */
#estimateTabs .k-tabstrip-items .k-link:hover {
    background: #e6f2ff !important;
    color: #000;
}

/* Active tab */
#estimateTabs .k-tabstrip-items .k-state-active .k-link {
    background: #cce0ff !important;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #1e88e5;
    font-weight: 700;
}


This makes the tab bar:

Flat ribbon style (light blue strip).

Slim tabs (~22px tall).

Clear active underline for selection.

Much less vertical space consumed inside popup.
